1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on link prediction in social networks, which falls under this sub-category. 
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the challenges in evaluating dynamic link prediction methods, which can be relevant to software engineering. 
3. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) - The paper deals with social networks and their analysis, which is a key area of computational social science. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses various link prediction methods, some of which may involve machine learning techniques. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a unified metric for evaluating link prediction accuracy, which can be relevant to data structures and algorithms.
